At least five people were injured when private security guards used rubber bullets to disperse protesters at a mining company in Marikana near Rustenburg on Tuesday, North West police said Spokesperson Colonel Adele Myburgh said the 8am march at the company had been approved. “Half-an-hour into the march, private security officers allegedly fired rubber bullets at a group of protesters. Five people were injured and taken to a medical facility.” She said  police were investigating the incident. READ MORE: No police officer has been prosecuted for Marikana involvement – NPA Residents in Wonderkop were reported to have staged a legal protest outside Glencore mine in Marikana demanding employment. – African News Agency